cs.AR, cs.CV, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.NE

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) sub-category as it proposes an efficient algorithm for performing fast convolutions on CPUs with significant amounts of shared L3 cache. It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as convolutional layers are commonly used in image processing tasks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it discusses optimizing algorithms for modern CPUs. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as convolutional layers are commonly used in neural networks.
